This paper deals with improving the performance of sequence tagging models for information extraction in the medical domain. The use of syntactic patterns is a key feature in this improvement. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also deals with information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (LG), which are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the use of neural models suggests the sub-category of artificial intelligence (AI). Finally, the paper deals with medical applications, which could fall under the sub-category of cybernetics (CY).
